                        <span class="blogHeadline">Source Code available</span>
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <small>Sunday, October 31st, 2010</small>

                <div>
                    <div class="en"><strong>WARNING:</strong> This is a development post. So if you're not into programming, you might find it pretty boring...
<br />&nbsp;<br />
<a href="http://joyridelabs.de/img/blog/haskellNikki.png"><img title="Nikki on a sequential operator" src="http://joyridelabs.de/img/blog/haskellNikki_scaled.png" alt="Nikki on a sequential operator" width="446" height="271" /></a>
<br />&nbsp;<br />
Our source code repository is now publicly available. So, if you know <a href="http://haskell.org/" target="_blank">Haskell</a> and/or want to get your hands dirty, point your browser to <a href="http://joyridelabs.de/game/code/">http://joyridelabs.de/game/code/</a>.</div>
                </div>
                <p class="blog">
        Tags: <a href="http://joyridelabs.de/blog//?tag=business" rel="tag">business</a>, <a href="http://joyridelabs.de/blog//?tag=game-tech" rel="tag">game tech</a>, <a href="http://joyridelabs.de/blog//?tag=nikki" rel="tag">nikki</a>, <a href="http://joyridelabs.de/blog//?tag=opensource" rel="tag">open source</a>, <a href="http://joyridelabs.de/blog//?tag=other" rel="tag">other</a>, <a href="http://joyridelabs.de/blog//?tag=press" rel="tag">press</a><br />    <a href="http://joyridelabs.de/blog/?p=479#respond" title="Comment on Source Code available">No Comments &#187;</a></p>
